## Requirement 1: Node.js/NPX in PATH

**What this checks**: Whether Cursor can find `npx` command to launch the MCP server

**🚨 FIRST: Ask How User Launches Cursor**

Before running any diagnostics, ask:
> "How do you normally open Cursor? From Spotlight/Raycast, or from the terminal?"

**If Spotlight/Raycast**: This is likely the problem! `dev` (via `shadowenv`) sets up PATH correctly only when you launch from terminal. Tell user:
> "Try launching Cursor from your terminal instead: `cd ~/src/your-project && cursor .`"

This simple change fixes the majority of "spawn npx ENOENT" errors.

---

**CRITICAL INSIGHT**: Node.js can be installed THREE different ways:
1. **NVM** (Recommended by Shopify) - Requires `.zshrc` configuration
2. **Homebrew (Apple Silicon)** - Works automatically at `/opt/homebrew/bin/node`
3. **Homebrew (Intel)** - Legacy, located at `/usr/local/bin/node`

**Each has different PATH requirements!**

### Comprehensive Verification (Checks All Three)
```bash
echo "=== Node.js Comprehensive Health Check ===" && \
echo "" && \
echo "1. Current Node Status:" && \
which node && node --version || echo "❌ Node not found in PATH" && \
echo "" && \
echo "2. Current NPX Status:" && \
which npx && npx --version || echo "❌ NPX not found in PATH" && \
echo "" && \
echo "3. Check NVM Installation:" && \
if [ -d ~/.nvm ]; then \
  echo "✅ NVM directory exists at ~/.nvm"; \
  ls ~/.nvm/versions/node 2>/dev/null | head -3 || echo "   (No Node versions installed in NVM)"; \
else \
  echo "❌ NVM not installed"; \
fi && \
echo "" && \
echo "4. Check NVM .zshrc Configuration:" && \
if grep -q "^export NVM_DIR" ~/.zshrc 2>/dev/null; then \
  echo "✅ NVM configured in .zshrc:"; \
  grep "NVM_DIR" ~/.zshrc | grep -v "^#" | head -3; \
else \
  echo "❌ NVM not configured in .zshrc (or lines are commented out)"; \
fi && \
echo "" && \
echo "5. Check Homebrew Apple Silicon Node:" && \
if [ -f /opt/homebrew/bin/node ]; then \
  echo "✅ Homebrew Node (Apple Silicon) installed:"; \
  /opt/homebrew/bin/node --version; \
else \
  echo "❌ No Homebrew Node (Apple Silicon)"; \
fi && \
echo "" && \
echo "6. Check Homebrew Intel Node (Legacy):" && \
if [ -f /usr/local/bin/node ]; then \
  echo "✅ Homebrew Node (Intel) installed:"; \
  /usr/local/bin/node --version; \
else \
  echo "❌ No Homebrew Node (Intel)"; \
fi && \
echo "" && \
echo "7. Determine Active Node Source:" && \
NODE_PATH=$(which node 2>/dev/null) && \
if [ -n "$NODE_PATH" ]; then \
  if [[ "$NODE_PATH" == *".nvm"* ]]; then \
    echo "🟢 Active: NVM (Shopify recommended) → $NODE_PATH"; \
  elif [[ "$NODE_PATH" == *"/opt/homebrew"* ]]; then \
    echo "🟡 Active: Homebrew Apple Silicon (works but not recommended) → $NODE_PATH"; \
  elif [[ "$NODE_PATH" == *"/usr/local"* ]]; then \
    echo "🟡 Active: Homebrew Intel Legacy (works but not recommended) → $NODE_PATH"; \
  else \
    echo "🟠 Active: Unknown source → $NODE_PATH"; \
  fi; \
else \
  echo "🔴 No Node currently in PATH"; \
fi
```

