## 🔧 Fix Scenarios Based on Diagnostic Results

### Scenario 1: No Node At All (🔴 Fresh Install Needed)

**Symptoms:**
- "❌ Node not found in PATH"
- "❌ NPX not found in PATH"
- "❌ NVM not installed"
- "❌ NVM not configured in .zshrc"
- "❌ No Homebrew Node" (both locations)
- "🔴 No Node currently in PATH"

**This means:** User has NEVER installed Node.js

**Fix Option A: Install via NVM (⭐ Shopify Recommended)**

```bash
echo "🔧 Installing Node.js via NVM (Shopify recommended method)"

# Step 1: Install NVM
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

# Step 2: Configure .zshrc (NVM installer may do this automatically, but verify)
if ! grep -q "NVM_DIR" ~/.zshrc; then
  echo 'export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"' >> ~/.zshrc
  echo '[ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"  # This loads nvm' >> ~/.zshrc
  echo '[ -s "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/bash_completion"  # This loads nvm bash_completion' >> ~/.zshrc
  echo "✅ Added NVM configuration to .zshrc"
else
  echo "✅ NVM already configured in .zshrc"
fi

# Step 3: Reload shell to activate NVM
source ~/.zshrc

# Step 4: Install Node.js 20 (LTS - matches Shopify dev environment)
nvm install 20

# Step 5: Verify installation
echo "" && echo "=== Verification ===" && \
which node && node --version && \
which npx && npx --version
```

**Expected output:**
```
✅ Added NVM configuration to .zshrc

=== Verification ===
/Users/[username]/.nvm/versions/node/v20.x.x/bin/node
v20.x.x
/Users/[username]/.nvm/versions/node/v20.x.x/bin/npx
10.x.x
```

**Fix Option B: Install via Homebrew (⚠️ Alternative Method)**

```bash
echo "🔧 Installing Node.js via Homebrew (alternative method)"

# Check if Homebrew is installed
if ! command -v brew &> /dev/null; then
  echo "❌ Homebrew not installed. Installing Homebrew first..."
  /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
fi

# Install Node
brew install node

# Verify installation
echo "" && echo "=== Verification ===" && \
which node && node --version && \
which npx && npx --version
```

**Expected output:**
```
=== Verification ===
/opt/homebrew/bin/node      # Apple Silicon
v23.x.x (or current Homebrew version)
/opt/homebrew/bin/npx
10.x.x
```

**After installation:** Tell user to **fully restart Cursor** (Cmd+Q and reopen).

