### After ANY Node Fix: Full Cursor Restart Required

**🚨 CRITICAL - Tested and Confirmed:**

**ALWAYS do a full Cursor restart after Node/PATH fixes:**

```bash
# Press Cmd+Q in Cursor (or run: pkill -9 Cursor)
# Wait for Cursor to fully quit
# Reopen Cursor from Applications
```

**Why this matters:**
- ❌ **Toggle OFF/ON will NOT work** - subprocess inherits old PATH from Cursor's main process
- ✅ **Full restart WILL work** - Cursor re-reads `.zshrc` and picks up new PATH with Node/NPX

**Real-world confirmation**: User had this exact issue - npx worked in terminal but not in Cursor. Full restart fixed it immediately.

**Important:** After fixing Node, you MUST fully restart Cursor (Cmd+Q and reopen).
This is not optional - toggling the server will fail because it doesn't reload your PATH.

### Known Good Versions (Tested)
- **NVM**: 0.39.7
- **Node.js**: v20.11.0 (or any v20.x.x LTS)
- **npm/npx**: 10.2.4

